Heat the oil in a large frying pan and fry the onion, red pepper and garlic until soft.Add the walnuts and kidney beans to the pan and cook for a further 2-3 minutes.Add the rice to the pan, warm through and season with salt and freshly ground black pepper.Remove the pan from the heat and stir in the chopped chervil.Lightly oil a large bowl and pack the rice mixture into the bowl.To serve, turn the rice out onto a plate to make a dome shape.